WEBVTT

00:02.280 --> 00:02.980
<i>Previously on "Switched at Birth"...</i>

00:03.014 --> 00:04.515
I never felt at home at Buckner.

00:04.549 --> 00:06.650
Going to Carlton doesn't make any sense.

00:06.685 --> 00:08.552
They do have this new pilot program

00:08.586 --> 00:11.422
for kids with deaf
parents or deaf siblings.

00:11.456 --> 00:13.424
We need somebody that
everybody's familiar with.

00:13.458 --> 00:15.025
Like a brand.

00:15.060 --> 00:17.194
John, you're a leader.
You deserve a third act.

00:17.228 --> 00:18.162
Think about it.

00:18.196 --> 00:20.130
No turning back now.

00:20.165 --> 00:22.926
I thought maybe you wanted to know
that you had another one on the way.

00:22.927 --> 00:25.230
_

00:25.737 --> 00:27.938
She hates me for no
reason, other than the fact

00:27.972 --> 00:28.906
that I'm hearing.

00:31.976 --> 00:33.610
Look, I don't know what your deal is.

00:33.645 --> 00:36.413
If this is something about Emmett or...

00:36.414 --> 00:39.166
_

00:39.167 --> 00:42.811
_

00:46.391 --> 00:49.293
So I re-read "The Scarlet Letter"

00:49.327 --> 00:52.429
and I learned all of the relevant signs.

00:52.464 --> 00:54.364
"Adultery, "hypocrisy,"

00:54.399 --> 00:57.334
"who thought it was a good
idea to cast Demi Moore

00:57.402 --> 00:59.937
as Hester Prynne?" And I have not

00:59.971 --> 01:03.240
slowed down the class
once in the last week.

01:03.708 --> 01:07.015
_

01:08.179 --> 01:09.146
(Sighs) Well, uh,

01:09.180 --> 01:10.214
next up, Shakespeare.

01:10.248 --> 01:12.883
I may have to use up my sick days.

01:14.017 --> 01:16.379
_

01:16.380 --> 01:20.023
Yeah. Hey, um, maybe we can
even sit with your old crew.

01:27.398 --> 01:28.665
Or not.

01:36.441 --> 01:41.409
- synced and corrected by chamallow -
- www.addic7ed.com -

01:44.682 --> 01:45.716
Nice work.

01:48.620 --> 01:51.321
Noah. Pilot program.

01:51.356 --> 01:52.689
We have like every class together.

01:52.724 --> 01:55.292
Noah, I know who you are.

01:55.326 --> 01:57.528
There's only like seven of us.

01:57.562 --> 02:00.330
I'm sorry. Look, I'm distracted right now.

02:00.365 --> 02:03.233
Trying to fix this. Someone wrote
something really nasty on my locker.

02:03.268 --> 02:04.268
Oh, yeah.

02:04.302 --> 02:07.271
They shoved a note in mine too.

02:07.305 --> 02:08.672
There's Ms. Bledsoe.

02:08.705 --> 02:10.440
Maybe we should tell her.

02:10.475 --> 02:13.277
Uh, yeah. And add "rat"

02:13.311 --> 02:14.545
to my list of crimes
against deaf humanity?

02:14.579 --> 02:16.346
No, thank you.

02:19.759 --> 02:21.090
_

02:21.091 --> 02:23.253
Uhh...

02:23.288 --> 02:25.489
just personalizing my locker.

02:26.465 --> 02:28.592
_

02:28.593 --> 02:31.728
Uh, "let" may be too strong of a word.

02:33.993 --> 02:35.748
_

