Where's a volleyball
when you need one, huh?

02:54.319 --> 02:55.652
You heard about that?

02:55.687 --> 02:57.487
(Chuckles)

03:01.426 --> 03:03.627
<i>Daphne: Something happened.
But Bay won't say what.</i>

03:03.661 --> 03:07.631
Some of the deaf kids don't
like the pilot program.

03:07.665 --> 03:10.634
You'd think that people who
had been bullied themselves

03:10.668 --> 03:13.303
would be the last ones
to do it to someone else.

03:15.340 --> 03:16.406
But Bay's all right?

03:16.441 --> 03:17.641
She seems to be.

03:19.611 --> 03:22.312
Can you finish up?

03:22.347 --> 03:23.513
<i>My telenovela is on.</i>

03:23.548 --> 03:26.583
Mom, wait. I need to talk to you.

03:26.618 --> 03:27.584
Both of you.

03:27.619 --> 03:29.353
<i>I know that tone.</i>

03:29.387 --> 03:31.288
- Angelo.
- Yes.

03:31.322 --> 03:32.289
It's Angelo.

03:33.591 --> 03:34.791
He's gonna be a father again.

03:34.826 --> 03:36.760
- What?!
- You're pregnant?!

03:36.794 --> 03:38.428
No. Not me.

03:38.463 --> 03:40.731
He got someone else pregnant?

03:42.500 --> 03:43.467
Yeah.

03:43.501 --> 03:44.668
Of course he did.

03:44.702 --> 03:47.337
Do we know who she is?

03:47.372 --> 03:49.539
Her name is Lana.

03:49.574 --> 03:51.608
And she's a medical student at U.M.K.C.

03:53.745 --> 03:54.778
Young. Of course.

03:54.812 --> 03:58.415
<i>They met on the plane going back to Italy.</i>

03:58.449 --> 04:00.417
(Chuckling) Oh, that's just perfect.

04:00.451 --> 04:02.586
Mom! Please. Can I get through this?

04:02.620 --> 04:03.787
Is she African-American?

04:03.821 --> 04:05.689
- Pretty?
- Yeah.

04:06.824 --> 04:08.558
You know her?

04:08.593 --> 04:10.560
She came to the court looking for Angelo,

04:10.595 --> 04:12.763
and both Bay and Daphne met her.

04:12.797 --> 04:14.498
They just didn't know who she was.

04:14.532 --> 04:16.833
Bay knows?

04:16.868 --> 04:18.402
Everyone knows.

04:19.437 --> 04:22.639
I'm sorry I didn't tell
you when I found out.

04:22.674 --> 04:24.808
But I knew what you would say.

04:24.842 --> 04:27.511
And it seemed as if you and Angelo
had finally buried the hatchet.

04:27.545 --> 04:29.780
I know where I'd like to bury a hatchet.

04:29.814 --> 04:31.682
<i>Isn't your novela starting?</i>

04:31.716 --> 04:34.651
Yes, but they're bound to be a letdown.

04:34.686 --> 04:36.586
<i>Nothing they write in the telenovelas</i>

04:36.621 --> 04:38.755
can hold a candle to Angelo's real life.

04:43.828 --> 04:45.696
<i>(Door closes)</i>

04:45.730 --> 04:46.863
I'm sorry, honey.

04:46.898 --> 04:50.534
Honestly, it really doesn't affect me.

04:50.568 --> 04:51.535
Are you okay?

04:51.569 --> 04:53.804
I really thought he had changed.

04:55.606 --> 04:57.808
Hey, do you remember that day spa

04:57.842 --> 04:59.676
that you and I went to when I

04:59.711 --> 05:01.812
hurt my shoulder playing basketball?

05:01.846 --> 05:03.547
Yeah.

05:03.581 --> 05:05.716
Let's go there again. This weekend.

05:05.750 --> 05:07.451
Just you and me.

05:07.485 --> 05:10.387
It'll be a "suck it, Angelo" spa party.

05:10.421 --> 05:11.555
And he can pay for it.

05:11.589 --> 05:13.357
I'll use the money from the food truck.

05:14.425 --> 05:16.426
That sounds fantastic.

05:16.461 --> 05:17.594
Perfect.

05:22.867 --> 05:24.568
Ivan: For the first few events,

05:24.602 --> 05:26.737
- you'll be preaching totally to the choir.
- John: Uh-huh.

05:26.771 --> 05:28.472
Give you a chance to work out

05:28.506 --> 05:29.673
- your stump speech.
- Okay.

05:29.707 --> 05:31.641
Oh, and Kathryn, we've got you booked

05:31.676 --> 05:33.643
on Dara Walker's radio show.

05:33.678 --> 05:35.645
So you can share your favorite recipe

05:35.680 --> 05:37.681
- with all of her listeners.
- Great.

05:37.715 --> 05:39.483
Sorry to interrupt. Uh, mom, can I borrow

05:39.517 --> 05:40.484
your car again?

05:40.518 --> 05:42.452
I gotta go to rehearsal.

05:42.487 --> 05:44.621
Oh, sure, honey. When
is yours gonna be fixed?

05:44.655 --> 05:45.689
Not till Saturday.

05:45.723 --> 05:47.491
<i>Thanks, though.</i>

05:47.525 --> 05:48.658
Okay, see you.

05:48.693 --> 05:50.827
Mm. Ivan, here's the thing.

05:50.862 --> 05:53.397
I'm not interested in
memorizing talking points.

05:53.431 --> 05:55.665
It's one of the things
that drives me crazy

05:55.700 --> 05:57.501
when I watch these national guys campaign.

05:57.535 --> 05:59.436
- It's just the same canned crap...
- (Ivan chuckles)

05:59.470 --> 06:01.671
over and over and over.

06:01.706 --> 06:03.740
And John's great at speaking off-the-cuff.

06:03.775 --> 06:05.776
We've been getting very
familiar with the issues.

06:05.810 --> 06:08.712
I'd like to focus on
education and immigration.

06:08.746 --> 06:09.746
And you will.

06:09.781 --> 06:11.415
When you get elected.

06:11.449 --> 06:13.650
During the campaign, the
trick is to keep it general.

06:13.684 --> 06:15.819
Pro-middle class, anti-big government.

06:15.853 --> 06:16.820
<i>But I think what</i>

06:16.854 --> 06:18.789
John has to say on

06:18.823 --> 06:20.757
<i>education and immigration</i>

06:20.792 --> 06:22.859
will really resonate with
people in our district.

06:22.894 --> 06:24.694
You're running in a conservative district

06:24.729 --> 06:26.930
in a solidly G.O.P. state.
People love you.

06:26.964 --> 06:30.534
All you have to do to get
elected is to be yourself,

06:30.568 --> 06:31.768
talk about your business successes

06:31.803 --> 06:33.737
and tell that great story
about the home run you hit

06:33.771 --> 06:34.771
in the '92 all-star game.

06:34.772 --> 06:37.774
You can't lose.

06:38.910 --> 06:40.644
Hey, this is the recipe you should share.

06:40.678 --> 06:42.646
These are delicious.

06:43.948 --> 06:45.582
I bought 'em.

06:45.616 --> 06:47.484
Hmm.

06:47.518 --> 06:50.654
I am gonna make stickers.

06:50.688 --> 06:53.423
If Natalie wants to fight
it out with graffiti,

06:53.458 --> 06:55.492
she picked the wrong girl.

06:55.829 --> 06:58.587
_

06:59.163 --> 07:01.198
She is the one who is throwing gasoline.

07:01.232 --> 07:03.266
And I've tried to make peace.

07:03.301 --> 07:06.269
And I'm trying to keep up,
but she just keeps hating me

07:06.304 --> 07:08.205
because I can hear.

07:08.239 --> 07:10.974
And that's like hating me

07:11.008 --> 07:13.877
because I have brown hair or brown eyes.

07:13.911 --> 07:16.847
There's nothing that I can do about it.

07:18.253 --> 07:21.574
_

07:21.575 --> 07:25.950
_

07:25.951 --> 07:28.531
_

07:30.294 --> 07:31.561
Wow, that sucks.

07:34.265 --> 07:38.201
But we didn't ask for any cuts.

07:38.236 --> 07:40.103
And if Natalie and her posse

07:40.138 --> 07:42.139
keep taking it out on the hearing kids,

07:42.173 --> 07:43.294
we're just gonna fight back.

