Noah, right?

14:23.895 --> 14:25.763
No, Jeremy.

14:25.797 --> 14:27.832
(Chuckles)

14:27.866 --> 14:29.707
There better not be
contraband in there, camper.

14:29.735 --> 14:32.536
And if there is? But I'm willing to share.

14:32.571 --> 14:34.438
Ah, I really don't see a problem then.

14:34.473 --> 14:35.673
(Chuckles)

14:35.707 --> 14:37.675
Whoa, how much contraband
have you consumed?

14:37.709 --> 14:39.543
(Exhales)

14:39.578 --> 14:41.712
Noah, whoa! Are you okay?

14:41.780 --> 14:43.447
(Exhales deeply)

14:43.482 --> 14:44.448
I just need a minute.

14:44.483 --> 14:46.484
(Clears throat)

14:46.518 --> 14:48.352
What's going on?

14:50.222 --> 14:52.456
Um...

14:52.491 --> 14:55.292
I have this thing

14:55.327 --> 14:56.494
called Meniere's disease.

14:56.528 --> 14:58.195
(Sniffs)

14:58.230 --> 15:00.431
It messes with my... my
balance and my hearing and stuff.

15:05.303 --> 15:07.037
What do you mean "messes with"?

15:07.072 --> 15:10.174
Uh, I just get dizzy spells.

15:10.208 --> 15:13.144
They last for a few minutes or all day.

15:13.178 --> 15:15.079
<i>I've lost 60% of the
hearing in my right ear.</i>

15:15.113 --> 15:17.815
And eventually...

15:17.849 --> 15:19.483
I could lose it all.

15:19.518 --> 15:22.720
<i>When we went around in
the circle that first day,</i>

15:22.754 --> 15:24.388
I thought you said you were at Carlton

15:24.422 --> 15:25.723
because you had deaf relatives.

15:25.757 --> 15:27.324
Yeah, my Uncle.

15:27.359 --> 15:28.626
He's got Meniere's too.

15:28.660 --> 15:29.693
<i>- (Chuckles)
- Right.</i>

15:29.694 --> 15:32.116
My parents figured that it'd be good

15:32.150 --> 15:34.385
to get a head start on
the whole hand thing.

15:36.221 --> 15:38.322
It's incredible, you know?

15:38.356 --> 15:40.324
One day you're fine, and the next...

15:40.358 --> 15:42.059
whole life changes.

15:45.097 --> 15:46.764
Yeah.

15:46.798 --> 15:48.733
It's crazy how that can happen.

15:49.968 --> 15:51.969
Why didn't you just tell everybody

15:52.003 --> 15:53.738
that you have Meniere's?

15:53.772 --> 15:56.474
I don't really like to talk about it.

15:57.809 --> 16:00.277
Well...

16:00.312 --> 16:03.314
you wanna hear my "your whole
life changes in a day" story?

16:04.483 --> 16:05.516
(Chuckling) You've got one too?

16:05.550 --> 16:07.384
Get comfortable.

16:07.419 --> 16:09.286
<i>(Noah chuckles)</i>

16:09.321 --> 16:13.491
<i>Bay: Um, so we took this blood
test in bio class and, well...</i>

16:17.511 --> 16:20.313
<i>Jane: Welcome. I can see you're
all very excited to be here.</i>

16:20.348 --> 16:23.416
Well, you have been
selected to participate

16:23.451 --> 16:25.452
in this team-building weekend because...

16:25.486 --> 16:28.288
<i>you are either a role model at Carlton,</i>

16:28.322 --> 16:30.323
<i>a troublemaker...</i>

16:30.358 --> 16:32.125
<i>or a target.</i>

16:32.159 --> 16:33.426
<i>Your first assignment</i>

16:33.461 --> 16:35.395
will be to replicate

16:35.429 --> 16:38.331
<i>the object that's under this tarp.</i>

16:38.366 --> 16:40.233
<i>You will be split up
into groups of five...</i>

16:41.802 --> 16:44.804
<i>one looker, two runners</i>

16:44.839 --> 16:46.740
<i>and two builders.</i>

16:47.975 --> 16:49.042
<i>You'll get the hang of it.</i>

16:49.076 --> 16:50.610
<i>Now before you start out,</i>

16:50.645 --> 16:52.846
<i>please remember: You must always sign.</i>

16:54.448 --> 16:55.482
<i>Okay.</i>

16:55.516 --> 16:56.650
First group:

16:56.684 --> 16:59.286
<i>Daphne.</i>

17:00.421 --> 17:02.188
<i>Natalie.</i>

17:02.223 --> 17:03.323
Jane: Bay.

17:05.126 --> 17:06.992
<i>Noah.</i>

17:07.028 --> 17:08.161
<i>And Emmett.</i>

17:12.934 --> 17:15.268
<i>Second group:</i>

17:15.303 --> 17:17.737
<i>Jennifer.</i>

17:17.771 --> 17:19.705
<i>Tony.</i>

17:19.740 --> 17:21.107
<i>Amy.</i>

17:21.142 --> 17:22.709
<i>Howard.</i>

17:22.742 --> 17:24.944
<i>And Liz.</i>

17:24.979 --> 17:26.880
So Kathryn, what do you call this dish?

17:26.914 --> 17:27.847
Just what it is...

17:27.882 --> 17:29.849
pork chops, black beans

17:29.884 --> 17:32.452
- and salsa.
- That is so good!

17:32.486 --> 17:35.422
Now I taste the cinnamon. But what else?

17:35.456 --> 17:38.491
Cumin, a little chili powder, ginger.

17:38.526 --> 17:40.160
It's a rub.

17:40.194 --> 17:42.362
And can you tell our listeners
how you came up with this

17:42.396 --> 17:44.130
delectable combination?

17:45.399 --> 17:47.867
Actually, um...

17:47.902 --> 17:49.803
I got this recipe a long time ago

17:49.837 --> 17:51.104
from this guy who works for John

17:51.138 --> 17:53.673
at the car wash... Hector Gonzales.

17:53.708 --> 17:57.544
I believe it's a variation
on a Guatemalan dish.

17:57.578 --> 17:58.845
- Interesting.
- Yeah.

17:58.879 --> 18:01.815
Hector started out on the
line at John's first car wash.

18:01.849 --> 18:03.350
And when he opened two more,

18:03.384 --> 18:04.651
he promoted him to manager.

18:04.685 --> 18:05.685
He did a great job.

18:05.720 --> 18:07.454
Is that when he gave you this recipe?

18:07.488 --> 18:09.356
I... I...

18:09.390 --> 18:10.390
I don't quite remember.

18:10.424 --> 18:12.125
But it's so great because

18:12.159 --> 18:15.228
John never forgets that we
are a nation of immigrants.

18:15.262 --> 18:17.230
And he believes that we should be finding

18:17.264 --> 18:19.933
legal ways to welcome people

18:19.967 --> 18:22.902
who want to be part of
this great American dream.

18:22.937 --> 18:24.871
Not putting up barriers to push them out.

18:24.905 --> 18:26.673
That is very admirable.

18:27.842 --> 18:30.910
Does your family eat a lot
of Latin-inspired dishes?

18:30.945 --> 18:33.813
We're very inclusive.

18:33.848 --> 18:35.582
We eat all kinds of food.

18:38.586 --> 18:39.552
(Exhales)

18:39.587 --> 18:41.654
So can I burn this thing now?

18:41.689 --> 18:44.391
I'm afraid the news isn't good.

18:44.425 --> 18:46.226
But I'm feeling better.

18:46.260 --> 18:49.195
That's because you haven't been doing
anything to irritate the problem.

18:49.230 --> 18:51.965
Cutting hair, signing, painting.

18:51.999 --> 18:53.233
The M.R.I. shows the beginnings

18:53.267 --> 18:56.069
of osteonecrosis in your wrists.

18:56.103 --> 18:57.937
And that's bad?

18:59.140 --> 19:00.073
It can be.

19:04.812 --> 19:07.013
If you don't make some changes soon,

19:07.048 --> 19:09.682
it'll be hard to turn a doorknob,

19:09.717 --> 19:12.485
hold a hairbrush, drive a car.

19:14.488 --> 19:16.623
Okay, so what do I need
to do to make it better?

19:16.657 --> 19:17.624
At this point,

19:17.658 --> 19:19.459
it's about not making it worse.

19:19.493 --> 19:21.494
(Sighs)

19:21.529 --> 19:23.263
I'll just find someone else.

19:24.298 --> 19:25.398
Regina.

19:26.467 --> 19:28.968
You've seen over a dozen specialists.

19:29.003 --> 19:31.905
At some point it's not about giving up.

19:31.939 --> 19:35.075
It's just simply about
accepting your new reality.

19:38.879 --> 19:40.080
<i>(Pop music playing)</i>

19:40.114 --> 19:42.749
<i>* I waited for your call</i>

19:42.783 --> 19:45.718
<i>* and for the moon</i>

19:45.753 --> 19:49.556
<i>* to release me from the
longest afternoon... *</i>

19:50.791 --> 19:54.461
All right, an art project.
We are so gonna win this.

19:54.462 --> 19:57.642
_

19:57.698 --> 19:59.632
Okay, I didn't get all of that,

19:59.667 --> 20:01.634
<i>- but I'm pretty sure it was insulting.
- _</i>

20:01.635 --> 20:03.035
_

20:04.532 --> 20:06.228
_

20:06.229 --> 20:08.441
_

20:08.442 --> 20:10.243
What's Noah doing?

20:10.803 --> 20:13.510
- _
- _

20:13.511 --> 20:16.978
- _
- _

20:19.987 --> 20:21.754
Hey, are you okay?

20:21.789 --> 20:22.856
I'm fine, I'm fine.

20:22.890 --> 20:24.891
Um, I just wanted to ask, um...

20:24.925 --> 20:26.993
Daphne, uh, for more...

20:27.027 --> 20:28.795
uh... (Exhales)

20:28.829 --> 20:29.996
Uh, paper, pen?

20:30.030 --> 20:31.898
- Your palm's itchy?
- No no no, um...

20:31.932 --> 20:32.966
- How do you sign "information"?
- Oh, uh,

20:33.000 --> 20:34.634
- "information."
- Information. Okay, sorry.

20:34.668 --> 20:35.835
Ms. Bledsoe

20:35.870 --> 20:37.637
<i>said that, uh,</i>

20:37.671 --> 20:38.738
the, um...

20:38.772 --> 20:39.772
Uhh, Daphne?

20:39.807 --> 20:41.441
Oh, uh, the lookers!

20:41.475 --> 20:42.408
The lookers, yes.

20:42.443 --> 20:44.377
The can come to the, uh...

20:44.411 --> 20:45.478
Uh, the fence!

20:45.513 --> 20:46.479
Thank you.

20:46.514 --> 20:48.214
Um, so we don't

20:48.249 --> 20:51.151
have to run so far if we need

20:51.185 --> 20:52.318
information.

20:52.353 --> 20:53.386
Yes!

20:53.420 --> 20:55.054
Yes, I knew them all.
Knew all those signs.

20:55.089 --> 20:56.990
Ha ha! First sentence!

20:57.024 --> 20:58.191
<i>(Chuckles)</i>

20:58.225 --> 20:59.926
<i>(Wood rattles)</i>

21:01.962 --> 21:04.097
And I'm back to being
completely in the dark again.

21:04.131 --> 21:05.052
Okay, now, she's asking

21:05.065 --> 21:06.499
what we are supposed

21:06.534 --> 21:08.568
to do with all this stuff.

21:08.602 --> 21:09.569
Okay okay.

21:12.766 --> 21:15.315
_

21:15.316 --> 21:19.089
_

21:19.513 --> 21:20.446
You and me?

21:20.447 --> 21:21.447
_

21:22.750 --> 21:24.584
Okay. Um, maybe.

21:26.189 --> 21:28.650
_

21:28.656 --> 21:31.224
Because he's my friend.

21:31.258 --> 21:33.238
And he's not feeling well.

21:33.239 --> 21:35.306
_

21:35.396 --> 21:37.130
No no, it's not like that.

21:37.164 --> 21:38.881
Look, it's hard to explain.

21:38.882 --> 21:40.176
_

21:41.102 --> 21:42.702
<i>Noah: I think we know what to do now.</i>

21:48.085 --> 21:49.719
Lana: Does everybody know?

21:49.754 --> 21:51.688
In your family?

21:51.722 --> 21:53.656
Uh, about you and Angelo?

21:53.691 --> 21:55.525
Yeah, kinda.

21:55.559 --> 21:58.528
Ah, but don't worry, we've
all been fooled by Angelo

21:58.562 --> 21:59.796
at some time or another.

22:01.465 --> 22:02.599
He's a charming guy.

22:02.633 --> 22:05.235
I wouldn't really know.

22:05.269 --> 22:06.403
I barely know him.

22:07.471 --> 22:09.239
I don't normally

22:09.273 --> 22:10.194
meet somebody and then...

22:10.207 --> 22:12.242
I mean, I... I... I'm saying

22:12.276 --> 22:14.244
I... I'm not some kind of...

22:14.278 --> 22:18.014
Oh, yeah. I'm sure you're not.

22:20.117 --> 22:23.153
So you're not like ready
to have the baby, are you?

22:23.187 --> 22:25.221
I don't think so.

22:25.256 --> 22:26.823
Good. I didn't pay attention

22:26.857 --> 22:28.892
to those birthing videos in health class,

22:28.926 --> 22:30.026
so I wouldn't be much help.

22:30.061 --> 22:31.661
Well, you don't have to worry.

22:31.695 --> 22:33.930
<i>- I'm a medical student.
- They teach you how to...</i>

22:33.964 --> 22:35.832
deliver your own baby in medical school?

22:35.866 --> 22:37.667
- (Inhaling and exhaling deeply)
- Are you okay?

22:37.701 --> 22:39.002
- Look out!
- Oh!

22:39.036 --> 22:40.570
- (Tires screech)
- (Car crashes)

22:40.604 --> 22:41.571
(Both panting)

22:45.708 --> 22:47.675
- Thanks, man. Sorry.
- Yeah.

22:53.349 --> 22:54.382
Are you sure you're okay?

22:54.416 --> 22:55.416
I'm fine. I just...

22:55.451 --> 22:57.151
I feel terrible about your car.

22:57.186 --> 22:59.354
I mean, if you weren't taking me home...

22:59.388 --> 23:02.957
I could be in a worse
accident on the freeway.

23:02.992 --> 23:03.958
(Moaning) Oh.

23:03.993 --> 23:05.193
(Inhales deeply and exhales)

23:05.194 --> 23:06.961
- Ooh, okay.
- Okay, we're going to the hospital.

23:06.996 --> 23:08.229
No, it's just Braxton-Hicks.

23:08.263 --> 23:09.931
It's... they're practice contractions.

23:09.965 --> 23:11.799
They're perfectly harmless...

23:11.834 --> 23:13.067
(Groans)

23:13.102 --> 23:15.803
I think.

23:15.838 --> 23:17.071
Yep, definitely going to the hospital.

23:17.106 --> 23:18.673
Here we go.

23:18.707 --> 23:19.941
(Groans)

23:19.975 --> 23:23.645
Jane: So how do you all think that went?

23:27.683 --> 23:28.783
<i>Matthew?</i>

23:28.817 --> 23:30.551
How'd it go for you and your group?

23:31.205 --> 23:32.332
_

23:33.154 --> 23:35.619
_

23:35.624 --> 23:37.125
<i>Maybe you should</i>

23:37.159 --> 23:39.093
try talking and see how
good you are at that?

23:39.128 --> 23:40.228
- Bay...
- Whoa whoa!

23:40.229 --> 23:41.997
_

23:42.031 --> 23:44.232
- That's not okay!
- (Overlapping arguing)

23:44.266 --> 23:46.267
<i>- Daphne: You should not be here!
- Noah: Calm down! Hey!</i>

23:46.301 --> 23:47.268
(Indistinct shouting)

23:47.302 --> 23:48.870
<i>Jane: Enough! Enough.</i>

23:50.939 --> 23:53.074
<i>That's what I thought.</i>

24:04.486 --> 24:06.454
<i>I want you to make a list</i>

24:06.488 --> 24:09.390
<i>of all the things that you think you know</i>

24:09.425 --> 24:11.259
<i>about your partner.</i>

24:11.293 --> 24:12.393
<i>And when you're done,
you'll share your insights</i>

24:12.428 --> 24:13.361
<i>with the group.</i>

24:14.530 --> 24:17.065
<i>Sign only. No interpreter.</i>

24:17.099 --> 24:18.299
<i>And remember:</i>

24:18.333 --> 24:21.069
You can't say anything related
to being hearing or deaf.

24:21.103 --> 24:22.804
<i>All right.</i>

24:22.838 --> 24:26.107
<i>Now I'm gonna break you into pairs.</i>

24:26.141 --> 24:27.075
<i>Bay</i>

24:27.109 --> 24:28.042
<i>and Natalie.</i>

24:29.078 --> 24:30.745
<i>Noah</i>

24:30.779 --> 24:33.614
<i>and Matthew.</i>

24:38.587 --> 24:40.788
I do have insurance, I promise.

24:40.823 --> 24:42.657
It's just in my other purse,

24:42.691 --> 24:45.393
which is moronic of me.

24:45.427 --> 24:48.296
Don't worry, we'll figure it out later.

24:48.330 --> 24:49.497
You don't have to stay.

24:49.531 --> 24:52.066
How else are you gonna get home?

24:52.101 --> 24:54.001
I'll figure something out.

24:54.036 --> 24:55.369
Are you sure you don't
want me to call somebody?

24:55.404 --> 24:57.839
<i>Angelo, maybe?</i>

24:57.873 --> 24:59.140
Okay, not Angelo.

24:59.174 --> 25:01.109
Um...

25:01.143 --> 25:02.944
someone from your family? Anybody?

25:04.780 --> 25:07.648
My family lives in Boston.

25:07.683 --> 25:09.751
And they don't even know I'm pregnant.

25:09.785 --> 25:12.453
<i>Nurse: Dr. Kornreich
thinks everything is fine.</i>

25:12.488 --> 25:14.722
But she wanted us to get an
ultrasound just to be sure.

25:16.458 --> 25:18.292
Are you the dad?

25:18.327 --> 25:19.460
Me? No. God, no.

25:19.495 --> 25:21.329
<i>I mean...</i>

25:21.363 --> 25:23.164
well, not because she's...

25:24.233 --> 25:26.033
we've never...

25:26.068 --> 25:27.401
I mean, we're not, you know...

25:27.436 --> 25:30.071
You know, we're just... we're friends.

25:30.105 --> 25:31.973
Yes. (Exhales)

25:32.007 --> 25:34.108
Um, I... I'll give you a minute.

25:34.143 --> 25:36.010
You can stay.

25:36.044 --> 25:38.012
<i>You know,</i>

25:38.046 --> 25:39.180
if you want to.

25:40.783 --> 25:41.983
Okay. Sure.

25:45.921 --> 25:46.888
There she is.

25:48.624 --> 25:50.792
<i>Toby: Wow.</i>

25:50.826 --> 25:53.561
That's incredible.

25:55.631 --> 25:58.599
Yeah. It's pretty amazing.

26:03.005 --> 26:05.907
I try not to look.

26:05.941 --> 26:07.942
It just makes it harder.

26:07.976 --> 26:09.277
Makes what harder?

26:09.311 --> 26:11.145
Giving her up for adoption.

26:14.883 --> 26:16.818
Oh.

26:18.620 --> 26:19.554
(Sighs)

26:23.525 --> 26:25.359
<i>Jane: All right, enough.</i>

26:25.394 --> 26:26.661
<i>Bay</i>

26:26.695 --> 26:28.563
<i>and Natalie, you're up.</i>

26:33.658 --> 26:34.910
_

26:36.271 --> 26:37.405
Look, if I have to...

26:37.406 --> 26:39.051
_

26:39.052 --> 26:42.908
_

26:43.946 --> 26:45.079
Okay. Fine, I'll start.

26:45.113 --> 26:47.849
Um, Natalie Pierce is a bully.

26:47.883 --> 26:49.183
<i>(Pen and paper clatter)</i>

26:52.333 --> 26:54.327
_

26:54.328 --> 26:58.558
_

26:58.894 --> 27:00.862
You don't know anything about me,

27:00.896 --> 27:04.532
but you hate me anyway,
which makes you a bigot

27:04.566 --> 27:05.499
and a bully.

27:05.500 --> 27:08.409
_

27:08.437 --> 27:12.440
Because every hearing person in the world

27:12.474 --> 27:13.441
is the same, right?

27:13.475 --> 27:15.376
We're all out to get you.

27:18.347 --> 27:20.248
<i>Jane: All right, settle down.</i>

27:20.315 --> 27:23.217
<i>Now that you've let off some steam,</i>

27:23.252 --> 27:25.119
try again.

27:25.153 --> 27:28.089
<i>But this time, say something positive</i>

27:28.123 --> 27:29.824
<i>about the other.</i>

27:38.867 --> 27:39.834
Proud.

27:41.904 --> 27:43.504
(Sighs and smacks lips)

27:43.553 --> 27:44.761
_

27:47.442 --> 27:48.542
Tough.

27:50.935 --> 27:52.421
_

27:54.416 --> 27:55.483
Honest.

27:57.670 --> 27:59.350
_

28:02.157 --> 28:03.090
<i>Jane: Excellent!</i>

28:03.125 --> 28:06.127
<i>And not so hard, right?</i>

28:06.161 --> 28:09.096
<i>I think we've all earned our s'mores.</i>

28:17.506 --> 28:19.607
Well, you missed all the fireworks.

28:19.641 --> 28:20.808
I caught a few.

28:20.842 --> 28:21.809
I'm gonna go get some s'mores.

28:21.843 --> 28:23.411
Hey!

28:23.445 --> 28:24.679
You're not wearing your brace.

28:24.713 --> 28:26.547
That means good news, right?

28:26.581 --> 28:28.416
Not exactly.

28:28.450 --> 28:29.617
Oh.

28:31.625 --> 28:34.835
_

28:34.836 --> 28:36.157
(Chuckling)

28:37.188 --> 28:39.887
_

28:40.095 --> 28:42.997
Yeah, did the doctor say
when you'd get better?

28:44.066 --> 28:45.132
She said the same thing

28:45.167 --> 28:46.868
that all the rest of them have said.

28:46.902 --> 28:49.670
That with the combination

28:49.705 --> 28:51.606
of learning to sign as an adult,

28:51.640 --> 28:53.507
the amount of signing that I've done

28:53.542 --> 28:55.710
and the painting and the
years of cutting hair,

28:55.744 --> 28:58.613
the damage is irreparable.

28:58.647 --> 29:00.414
And if I go back to doing what I was,

29:00.449 --> 29:03.251
it'll get worse.

29:03.285 --> 29:05.353
Chronic numbness, pain,

29:05.387 --> 29:07.188
severe arthritis.

29:08.390 --> 29:11.192
What about sign language?

29:15.163 --> 29:16.097
I can't.

29:17.165 --> 29:19.000
Ever?

29:21.069 --> 29:23.070
You can still sign to me.

29:23.105 --> 29:25.640
And I can understand it.

29:25.674 --> 29:26.707
You never know with medicine.

29:26.742 --> 29:28.876
New things are happening all the time.

29:30.846 --> 29:35.483
I... I need to go check on my group.

29:42.145 --> 29:45.050
_

29:45.051 --> 29:48.213
_

29:50.065 --> 29:51.332
Yes.

29:54.403 --> 29:55.336
What?

29:56.884 --> 29:59.936
_

30:00.876 --> 30:01.708
Meaning?

30:01.709 --> 30:06.426
_

30:07.082 --> 30:08.716
You think I'm faking this?

30:08.717 --> 30:11.412
_

30:11.682 --> 30:13.571
_

30:13.572 --> 30:15.913
_

30:15.914 --> 30:18.525
_

30:18.527 --> 30:20.394
If I could, why wouldn't I?

30:20.395 --> 30:21.502
_

30:21.503 --> 30:23.297
_

30:23.654 --> 30:25.912
_

30:26.435 --> 30:28.402
You are not in my body.

30:28.437 --> 30:30.972
You do not know how I feel.

30:31.006 --> 30:33.841
And if you really think that
I am not trying hard enough,

30:33.875 --> 30:36.911
you are most certainly not my friend.

30:51.384 --> 30:54.386
(Exhales and chuckles)

30:54.420 --> 30:56.121
I'm sorry.

30:56.155 --> 30:58.123
I, uh... I haven't figured out

30:58.157 --> 30:59.925
how to do that

30:59.959 --> 31:02.928
without, uh, scaring someone

31:02.962 --> 31:04.930
who can't hear me coming.

31:04.964 --> 31:07.132
It's okay.

31:07.166 --> 31:09.668
Are you okay?

31:09.702 --> 31:11.737
Can I help?

31:11.771 --> 31:16.642
Not unless you're a wizard or a magician.

31:16.676 --> 31:17.843
I don't think so.

31:17.877 --> 31:19.378
But, um,

31:19.412 --> 31:21.680
Harry Potter didn't find out

31:21.714 --> 31:24.383
that he was a wizard until he was like...

31:24.417 --> 31:25.350
15.

31:25.385 --> 31:26.585
So...

31:26.619 --> 31:28.186
there's always a chance.

31:28.221 --> 31:30.122
- 11.
- Hmm?

31:30.156 --> 31:32.357
Harry Potter was 11 when he
found out he was a wizard.

31:32.392 --> 31:33.392
Oh, right.

31:33.426 --> 31:34.426
My bad.

31:39.899 --> 31:44.136
I just found out that my mom
can't sign to me ever again.

31:46.639 --> 31:47.606
She has some

31:47.640 --> 31:50.575
weird physical thing

31:50.610 --> 31:52.644
messing up her hands.

31:55.748 --> 31:57.616
I'm sorry.

31:57.650 --> 32:00.319
You're not deaf. You don't get it.

32:00.353 --> 32:02.554
You have no idea how exhausting it is

32:02.588 --> 32:04.656
to have to read lips all the time.

32:04.691 --> 32:07.459
Imagine you found out that your parents

32:07.493 --> 32:10.362
could never talk to you
with their voice ever again.

32:12.265 --> 32:15.033
You had to sign with them
for the rest of your life.

32:18.004 --> 32:19.271
I'm imagining.

32:24.010 --> 32:26.011
If it you makes you, um,

32:26.045 --> 32:29.848
feel any better...

32:31.818 --> 32:35.520
she's probably a million
times madder than you are.

32:38.491 --> 32:41.360
It sucks to feel like
your body's betraying you.

32:48.000 --> 32:51.236
I'll see you back at camp.

32:51.270 --> 32:54.139
<i>- (Soft pop music playing)
- * thinking nothing is right</i>

32:54.173 --> 32:57.008
<i>* baby, come on</i>

32:57.043 --> 32:57.543
<i>* ooh</i>

33:01.080 --> 33:04.950
<i>* baby, come on.</i>

33:04.984 --> 33:06.551
(Sighs)

33:08.721 --> 33:11.423
- Hey.
- I just got off the phone with Ivan

33:11.457 --> 33:13.825
who told me that I need
to reign in my wife.

33:13.860 --> 33:16.361
<i>- Excuse me?
- Yeah.</i>

33:16.396 --> 33:18.630
<i>Guy's really got a way with
words, but the radio show...</i>

33:18.664 --> 33:20.565
you were just supposed
to talk about recipes.

33:23.269 --> 33:25.070
The only non-food thing

33:25.104 --> 33:27.372
I said was that you
believe that new immigrants

33:27.407 --> 33:29.141
should get a shot at the American dream.

33:29.175 --> 33:30.175
Is that so bad?

33:30.209 --> 33:31.376
Apparently Sawyer is
already spinning it...

33:31.411 --> 33:33.945
saying that I encourage
illegal immigration.

33:33.980 --> 33:35.180
But that's absurd. Hector's legal.

33:35.214 --> 33:36.748
All your guys are legal.

33:36.783 --> 33:37.749
But you didn't say that.

33:37.784 --> 33:39.151
(Scoffs)

33:39.185 --> 33:41.887
Fine, we'll go the press
tomorrow with the facts.

33:41.921 --> 33:43.889
No, the point is that it
is easy to make mistakes.

33:43.923 --> 33:46.658
That is why Ivan wants to
keep the message general.

33:46.692 --> 33:49.561
You know, we don't want to waste
time going on the defensive,

33:49.595 --> 33:50.695
doing damage control.

33:50.730 --> 33:52.464
So that's how you wanna win this thing?

33:52.498 --> 33:54.566
By saying nothing of substance?

33:54.600 --> 33:58.603
I have spent a lot of my life

33:58.638 --> 34:00.539
thinking I was just a dumb jock.

34:00.573 --> 34:01.573
That is your father talking.

34:01.607 --> 34:03.408
But if I am elected,

34:03.443 --> 34:05.410
I can really do something meaningful.

34:05.445 --> 34:09.347
I can make a difference in
how our kids are educated,

34:09.382 --> 34:11.248
in whether or not people get jobs,

34:11.284 --> 34:14.786
can own their own homes.
But I can't do that

34:14.821 --> 34:16.087
if I don't win.

34:16.121 --> 34:19.056
Then tell people your ideas.

34:19.091 --> 34:21.092
<i>Let them vote for something.</i>

34:21.127 --> 34:23.027
I'm sorry,

34:23.062 --> 34:25.764
but I think Ivan is right.

34:25.797 --> 34:27.632
If you're in the stronger position,

34:27.667 --> 34:29.634
you don't get aggressive,

34:29.668 --> 34:31.570
you hold steady and you let the other team

34:31.603 --> 34:32.571
make the mistakes.

34:34.373 --> 34:36.608
No more talking politics.

34:38.344 --> 34:40.277
Fine.

34:40.313 --> 34:42.214
Then consider your wife reigned in.

34:46.518 --> 34:50.222
Noah: (Off-key) * as the sun shines on

34:50.255 --> 34:52.991
♪ my face

34:53.025 --> 34:55.025
♪ it's true...

34:55.061 --> 34:56.895
Whoa! (Chuckles)

34:58.097 --> 35:00.065
Wow, payback's a bitch.

35:00.099 --> 35:01.199
Payback?

35:01.234 --> 35:03.802
Yeah, I snuck up on somebody earlier.

35:04.871 --> 35:06.638
(Chuckling) Never mind.

35:06.672 --> 35:07.639
How'd you find me here?

35:07.673 --> 35:09.508
Used my superpowers.

35:09.542 --> 35:11.610
I heard the singing. Don't tell anyone.

35:11.644 --> 35:12.777
Oh.

35:12.812 --> 35:14.513
Well, with my A.S.L. skills,

35:14.547 --> 35:15.680
I don't think you have to worry about me

35:15.715 --> 35:16.781
telling anybody anything.

35:16.816 --> 35:18.783
True.

35:18.818 --> 35:21.653
I just wanted some space.

35:21.687 --> 35:24.207
And I think your boyfriend wanted
to see a little less of me too.

35:24.724 --> 35:26.358
Come on.

35:26.392 --> 35:27.492
He was giving me the stink eye all day.

35:27.527 --> 35:28.567
I kind of put it together.

35:30.162 --> 35:31.496
Emmett's not my boyfriend.

35:33.299 --> 35:35.100
He was.

35:37.103 --> 35:39.037
What are you listening to anyway?

35:43.209 --> 35:44.743
Mm.

35:44.777 --> 35:46.077
Nice playlist.

35:46.112 --> 35:47.612
<i>Yeah.</i>

35:47.647 --> 35:49.881
I'm trying to commit them all to memory.

35:49.916 --> 35:51.783
You know, for when the...

35:51.817 --> 35:54.486
(Sighs)

35:54.520 --> 35:56.688
yeah, it sucks 'cause I really love music.

35:56.722 --> 35:58.490
So do Emmett and Daphne.

35:59.625 --> 36:02.294
Emmett's even in my brother's band.

36:02.328 --> 36:03.328
Seriously?

36:03.362 --> 36:05.130
Yeah.

36:05.164 --> 36:06.264
Am I an idiot?

36:06.299 --> 36:08.066
'Cause I don't really get that.

36:08.100 --> 36:10.435
I'm just saying going deaf may
not be what you think it is.

36:13.239 --> 36:14.372
I hope not.

36:17.843 --> 36:19.077
You wanna listen to something?

36:19.111 --> 36:22.213
Ooh, no signing and listening to music?

36:22.248 --> 36:23.848
Dangerous stuff.

36:23.883 --> 36:25.183
Living on the wild side here at

36:25.217 --> 36:27.297
<i>- the Carlton deaf school retreat.
- (Music playing)</i>

36:29.989 --> 36:32.958
<i>* I'm feeling your heart in mine *</i>

36:32.992 --> 36:33.692
<i>* ooh, yeah.</i>

36:40.482 --> 36:42.016
Poison Ivy.

36:42.050 --> 36:43.350
Yeah, uh,

36:43.385 --> 36:44.952
I got it too.

36:44.986 --> 36:46.153
Here.

36:46.188 --> 36:49.190
This stuff is like magic.

36:54.763 --> 36:56.764
Look, um, I really don't

36:56.798 --> 36:57.965
wanna go on another retreat.

36:58.751 --> 37:01.658
_

37:01.770 --> 37:02.837
Okay.

37:02.871 --> 37:05.606
So why don't we call a truce?

37:05.674 --> 37:09.810
The other kids can follow our example.

37:09.845 --> 37:11.545
No more retreats.

37:18.042 --> 37:18.970
_

37:19.354 --> 37:21.121
No problem.

37:31.166 --> 37:34.201
Okay, the car's coming around, so, uh...

37:34.236 --> 37:36.971
thanks for the ride.

37:37.005 --> 37:38.005
No problem.

37:38.039 --> 37:39.940
Hey, I can't stop thinking about

37:39.975 --> 37:41.842
what you said last night at the hospital.

37:41.877 --> 37:43.711
About putting the baby up for adoption

37:43.778 --> 37:45.679
and not having the family around.

37:45.714 --> 37:47.882
I shouldn't have even mentioned that.

37:47.916 --> 37:49.950
It's really not your problem.

37:49.985 --> 37:51.552
Oh, I know. It's just...

37:51.586 --> 37:52.987
the baby does have a family around.

37:53.021 --> 37:55.422
Other than Angelo.

37:55.457 --> 37:56.557
My sister.

37:56.591 --> 37:58.525
Her sister.

37:59.694 --> 38:01.362
Right.

38:01.396 --> 38:02.496
Bay.

38:02.530 --> 38:03.597
Yeah.

38:03.632 --> 38:06.267
I just thought maybe
you might wanna meet her

38:06.301 --> 38:10.371
and our family before you
make any final decisions.

38:12.007 --> 38:13.173
But that's it. That's all I had to say.

38:13.208 --> 38:15.075
So...

38:15.110 --> 38:16.043
I'll see you around.

38:16.077 --> 38:17.144
Okay.

38:29.724 --> 38:31.959
<i>(Door closes)</i>

38:45.473 --> 38:46.540
What are you doing?

38:46.574 --> 38:50.411
Checking out the city
college class catalog.

38:50.445 --> 38:52.446
Trying to figure out
what to do with myself

38:52.480 --> 38:55.382
now that I'm no longer a hairdresser.

38:55.417 --> 38:59.153
Maybe you should run for office like John.

38:59.187 --> 39:02.022
Don't think diplomacy is my strong suit.

39:02.057 --> 39:04.124
You think his is?

39:04.159 --> 39:06.126
(Light chuckle)

39:08.830 --> 39:11.198
Phlebotomist?

39:11.232 --> 39:16.570
Well, I don't love
needles or blood, but...

39:16.604 --> 39:17.805
I can learn. I'm tough.

39:18.807 --> 39:20.407
You are.

39:25.447 --> 39:29.516
I've been doing hair
since I was 19 years old.

39:29.551 --> 39:32.419
I was just a little older than you.

39:32.454 --> 39:34.355
I don't know what's next for me.

39:34.389 --> 39:36.156
I... I really don't.

39:43.898 --> 39:47.101
I do know what it means
not to be able to sign.

39:51.606 --> 39:52.773
You know I do.

39:55.944 --> 39:57.611
I... (Sighs)

39:57.645 --> 39:59.565
I have to figure out a
whole new life for myself.

40:00.648 --> 40:02.750
Everything I thought I had I...

40:04.719 --> 40:06.487
you never know how much
you depend on these things,

40:06.521 --> 40:08.155
huh?

40:14.029 --> 40:15.295
(Quietly) I'm sorry.

40:17.932 --> 40:18.966
I really am.

40:20.035 --> 40:21.835
I know.

40:27.809 --> 40:29.843
Hey. Okay, so,

40:29.878 --> 40:32.880
Natalie and I have called a truce

40:32.914 --> 40:36.050
which means no more retreats.

40:38.063 --> 40:40.352
_

40:41.856 --> 40:43.690
What's wrong?

40:44.530 --> 40:47.295
_

40:49.664 --> 40:53.467
Noah and I are just friends.

40:54.726 --> 40:56.067
_

40:57.534 --> 40:59.091
_

40:59.565 --> 41:00.835
_

41:01.838 --> 41:04.972
_

41:05.591 --> 41:09.354
_

41:11.019 --> 41:12.953
No.

41:13.642 --> 41:15.782
_

41:16.991 --> 41:18.725
Well, I know it must seem like that,

41:18.760 --> 41:19.960
but I really didn't.

41:19.961 --> 41:21.196
_

41:22.145 --> 41:24.153
_

41:25.767 --> 41:27.868
Emmett, my head is spinning.

41:27.902 --> 41:29.670
I... (Sighs)

41:29.704 --> 41:31.905
I just started this new school.

41:31.940 --> 41:34.675
I'm barely keeping up in classes.

41:34.709 --> 41:37.311
I mean, half the kids here hate me.

41:37.345 --> 41:38.027
I'm... I'm under water.

41:38.730 --> 41:39.713
_

41:40.815 --> 41:42.616
<i>- Well, then help me.
- (Piano music playing)</i>

41:42.650 --> 41:44.618
As my friend.

41:44.619 --> 41:46.200
_

41:47.529 --> 41:49.188
_

41:52.045 --> 41:54.719
_

41:54.720 --> 41:58.323
_

42:00.702 --> 42:02.703
But that's all that I
can handle right now.

42:02.737 --> 42:03.804
I'm sorry.

42:05.540 --> 42:08.775
<i>* I knew exactly what this</i>

42:08.810 --> 42:11.712
<i>- * would feel like
- _</i>

42:16.451 --> 42:19.486
<i>* I knew this day was coming</i>

42:19.521 --> 42:21.488
<i>* I knew it right from the start... *</i>

42:21.523 --> 42:22.756
Emmett.

42:28.663 --> 42:31.732
<i>* To hear the same voice</i>

42:31.766 --> 42:34.535
<i>* that said "hello"</i>

